<br>
As I write this, I say this as independently from any noble, social and family ties. These are words that I choose to speak from my own free will. Within I few months upon my return to Norrath, I shall be traveling towards the Northlands. Not in search for treasure or fame, but to follow the teachings or Tunare, Mother Of All. To Learn of the Northland and her peoples. Though I could come with no notice, but where would the fun in that be? <br>
<br>
I know that by justification alone of my heritage, I will be met by opposition from your clan, and others of the ilk. But my self mission is clear to me and with due respect, for a limited amount of time, I'd like to request that I, and possibly a fellow companion, be allowed safe travels into your homeland. Safe stay during the time there and then safe departure. Just so long as no harmful actions from me, or my possible companion, pass onto the Northland brave people. My request is only to ask permission to study, write songs and share stories with the brave warriors and shamans in the Northlands, so that these great works will not be lost to the education of others who study the area. But most importantly, if the gods strike down with their wrath, then the legends of the North will not be lost to the scholars of Norrath. This self mission is not assigned by any of my elders, I ask this of personal interest. <br>
<br>
The request, I humbly ask, be seriously considered. Sides, what is the worst that can be said? A simple no perhaps. Perhaps a multitude of various insults. That won't bother me. But the request is still the same. The knowledge of the Northland peoples will ring immortality to the heroes they sing about for future generations. To grant purpose to the great tributes they suffered and endured to become great. The request I ask, I ask in a civil tongue. I hope there can be a civil answer. <br>
<br>
Sincerely, <br>
Kittany Harlequin <br>
Songweaver of Tunare <br>
Loyal Sister to my Queen and Mother, Linamarae, of the Amazons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~fricka/shanks/teenyknot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Innkeep</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/13/01 9:49:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=709.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~fricka/sig/5fricka60x56.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *A Elaborate Scroll left in one of the mead halls of Hal</span><hr size=1> Fricka stepped away from the scroll with a frown on her face and a deep sadness in her eyes.<br>
